# .leak-denylist.example — template for the pre-commit leak guard (.githooks/pre-commit).
#
# Copy to .leak-denylist (which is gitignored) and add the strings you never want
# to commit — typically your internal hostnames. One extended-regex per line;
# blank lines and lines starting with '#' are ignored. Matching is case-insensitive.
#
# The built-in checks (tailnet 100.64/10 IPs, LEO-<number> ticket refs) always run;
# these are EXTRA patterns on top.
#
# Replace the placeholders below with your own (do NOT commit the real file):
# myproj-db
# myproj-app
# myproj-edge
# internal-vm-[0-9]+
# \.my-tailnet-name\.ts\.net
